article.headline: Fairleigh Dickinson 98, Lafayette 92
article.story: EASTON, Pa. (AP) -- Manny Ubilla scored 27 points and Sean Baptiste had 21 to lead Fairleigh Dickinson to a 98-92 victory over Lafayette on Friday night. John Galvin added 19 points for Fairleigh Dickinson (2-0). Bernell Murray had 12 points and Eric Hazard contributed 10. Ubilla sank 12 of his 13 free throw attempts and Galvin was 11-for-12. Andrew Brown and Bilal Abdullah each had 18 points to lead Lafayette (1-2), while Deirunas Visockas contributed 15 points and Jeff Kari had 10.
